ere isn’t the same level of comedy and invention: the level of sugary silliness is a little too high.</p>","headline":"Lou! review – France’s sickly sweet answer to Miranda Hart","trailText":"Ludivine Sagnier gives a cheerfully unflattering comic performance as a gawky single mum, but this sort of sugary confection doesn’t travel well","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/3/11/1426098967679/Ludivine-Sagnier-in-Lou-001.jpg","wordcount":"187","commentable":"true","starRating":"2","byline":"Peter Bradshaw","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-04-11T18:24:00+01:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/mar/12/lou-film-review-ludivine-sagnier-frances-answer-to-miranda-hart","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/mar/12/lou-film-review-ludivine-sagnier-frances-answer-to-miranda-hart","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/comedy","webTitle":"Comedy","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/comedy","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/comedy","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/film","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","sectionName":"Culture","references":[]},{"id":"tone/reviews","webTitle":"Reviews","type":"tone","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/tone/reviews","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/tone/reviews","references":[]},{"id":"film/ludivine-sagnier","webTitle":"Ludivine Sagnier","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/ludivine-sagnier","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/ludivine-sagnier","sectionName"