ich provide the film with a constant background beat – and crushing crust with giant stones at exactly the right moment. Director Farida Pacha and cinematographer Lutz Konermann transmute all this labour into a mesmerising, lyrical work about endurance, craftsmanship and family dynamics, all unfolding in a stunningly bleak landscape, where abandoned bicycles and machinery pepper the ground. Marcel Vaid’s score is aptly sparse, but seasons the images perfectly.</p>","headline":"My Name Is Salt review – a mesmerising, lyrical work","trailText":"The latest entry in the expanding subgenre of documentaries about food production is a beautifully made film about craftsmanship and endurance<br>","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/3/11/1426100032091/Seasonal-work---My-Name-I-001.jpg","wordcount":"145","commentable":"true","starRating":"4","byline":"Leslie Felperin","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-04-11T18:50:00+01:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/mar/12/my-name-is-salt-review-a-mesmerising-lyrical-documentary","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/mar/12/my-name-is-salt-review-a-mesmerising-lyrical-documentary","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/documentary","webTitle":"Documentary","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/documentary","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/documentary","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/film","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","sectionName":"Culture","references":[]},{"id":"tone/reviews","webTitle":"Reviews","typ