topsy","webPublicationDate":"2015-03-12T18:29:01Z","sectionId":"film","id":"film/2015/mar/12/mother-of-midnight-rider-victim-sarah-jones-shames-hollywood-reporter-for-publishing-autopsy","fields":{"shortUrl":"http://gu.com/p/46t6b","standfirst":"<p>The mother of the camera operator who died while filming a biopic of the southern rock musician Gregg Allman – leading to the imprisonment of its director – has expressed her shock that the US trade magazine printed details from her daughter’s autopsy report</p>","hasStoryPackage":"false","body":"<p>The mother of Sarah Jones, the camera operator whose death in a train accident led to the director of indie biopic Midnight Rider being jailed earlier this week, has written <a href=\"https://pmcvariety.files.wordpress.com/2015/03/open-letter-from-elizabeth-jones_3-12-15.pdf\">an open letter</a> chastising the Hollywood Reporter for publishing her daughter’s “gruesome” autopsy report.</p> <p>The US trade paper posted details of the autopsy online on Wednesday, before toning down their content later that day. Jones was killed in February 2014 in an accident on an active railroad bridge high over the Altamaha River in Wayne County, Georgia. Director Randall Miller become the first film-maker to be jailed for an on-set fatality in the US on Monday after pleading guilty to involuntary manslaughter and criminal trespass. </p> <p>The fatality occurred on the first day of shooting for Midnight Rider, a biopic of the southern rock musician Gregg Allman. Jones, 27, died when the train hit a metal frame bed that had been placed on the track as part of a dream sequence featuring actor William Hurt as Allman. Her death has galvanised safety campaigners in Hollywood, with a number of initiatives since introduced to improve conditions and encourage whistleblowers to report rogue operators.<br />Miller was sentenced to two years behind bars plus eight years of probation and a $20,000 (£13,250) fine on Monday after changing his plea to guilty in a deal which saw his wife and film-making partner Jody Savin walk free from court.</p> <p>Jones, who with her husband Richard has been at the forefront of work to improve safety on film sets since her daughter’s death, said she was “totally stunned” and “totally appalled” that the Hollywood Reporter had published the autopsy. Her letter is republished below.<br /></p> <blockquote class=\"quoted\"> <p>To The Hollywood Reporter:</p> <p>I am totally stunned, I am totally appalled, and I am ashamed of the callous reporter who leaked the autopsy report of our daughter for the world to see. Although the grace and beauty of Sarah Elizabeth Jones outshines the deprecating words on a page, no one, NO ONE, should be so low as to think this gruesome report is newsworthy.</p> <p>To the reporter, where is your own honor? Is your desire to climb the rungs of a career ladder so important that you infringe upon the privacy and civility of a family whose daughter was tragically hit by a train? Is our pain of losing a daughter not enough that you feel the need to exploit Sarah’s dignity?</p> <p>Shame on the tabloid that published the article, that it should be so crude and selfish for readership numbers? Does that not put you in the same category of selfishness as the movie producers who thought it was ok to steal a shot?</p> <p>Look at the lives of those you have harmed by publishing detail by detail, Sarah’s autopsy report. Do you not realize the pain and sadness of the Jones family? Do you not have an inkling of decency? Did the thought even occur to you that perhaps Sarah’s family did not choose to remember her by the poignant description of her remains?</p> <p>It is my hope for you that you will discover one goes much further and higher with greater respect and honor than sensationalism that is harmful to not only the one you are reporting on, but the surrounding community as well.</p> <p>It is my hope for you that you will find a place in the world of journalism that will not allow such indecency be a motivating facet of readership.</p> <p>It is my hope that the ones who are offended by this report will speak out and let The Hollywood Reporter know their thoughts.</p> <p><em>Elizabeth McCartha Jones, Sarah’s Mother</em></p> </blockquote>","headline":"Mother of Midnight Rider victim Sarah Jones shames Hollywood Reporter for publishing autopsy","trailText":"The mother of the camera operator who died while filming a biopic of the southern rock musician Gregg Allman – leading to the imprisonment of its director – has expressed her shock that the US trade magazine printed details from her daughter’s autopsy report","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2015/3/12/1426184020188/95ac9ae3-c856-4523-aea9-75cff42d7997-140x84.jpeg","wordcount":"602","commentable":"true","byline":"Ben Child","productionOffice":"UK","liveBloggingNow":"false","commentCloseDate":"2015-03-15T18:30:00+00:00"},"webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/mar/12/mother-of-midnight-rider-victim-sarah-jones-shames-hollywood-reporter-for-publishing-autopsy","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/2015/mar/12/mother-of-midnight-rider-victim-sarah-jones-shames-hollywood-reporter-for-publishing-autopsy","sectionName":"Film","tags":[{"id":"film/midnight-rider","webTitle":"Midnight Rider","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/midnight-rider","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/midnight-rider","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"film/film","webTitle":"Film","type":"keyword","sectionId":"film","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/film/film","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/film/film","sectionName":"Film","references":[]},{"id":"culture/culture","webTitle":"Culture","type":"keyword","sectionId":"culture","webUrl":"http://www.theguardian.com/culture/culture","apiUrl":"http://content.guardianapis.com/culture/culture","sectionName":"Culture","references":[]},{"id":"media/medi