No.' Now, I think, there's some consideration for it, but nothing definitive or even a skeletal version of what it would be.\"</p><p>\"I look forward to going down that road, if we could crack the nut,\" he said. \"I think the Banner/Hulk storylines [are] obviously not an easy nut to crack.\"</p><p></p><p>The Hulk has had a chequered history on the big screen, with neither 2003's Hulk nor 2008's The Incredible Hulk managing to win over fans on a grand scale. Ruffalo has had far greater praise in the role than either of his predecessors, Eric Bana and Ed Norton. But he remains wary of reintroducing the character as a standalone hero.</p><p></p><p>\"If they did Iron Man 4 and Banner's in that, that'd be very cool,\" he said. \"I'm on Tumblr, so I see a lot of Science Bros stuff, it's a very popular meme.\"</p><p></p><p>Marvel boss Kevin Feige said in 2012 that the comic books Planet Hulk and World War Hulk were both possible sources for new solo Hulk storylines, but admitted that each was problematic. \"I think there's pitfalls of continuity-overload, and mythology getting so dense that it almost collapses in on itself,\" he said. \"It happens every few decades or so in the comics. Apart from that, I'd say everything is on the table.\"</p><p></p><p>Planet Hulk sees the character banished from the Earth to become a gladiator in a far-flung solar system, while World War Hulk is about his return and subsequent revenge on the heroes – including Iron Man - who exiled him.</p><p></p><p>Ruffalo will next appear as The Hulk/Banner in The Avengers sequel Age of Ultron, which is due for release in May 2015.</p>","headline":"Marvel Studios 'considering' a new solo Hulk movie","trailText":"Hulk star Mark Ruffalo says studio's stance has shifted following runaway success of The Avengers","thumbnail":"http://static.guim.co.uk/sys-images/Guardian/Pix/pictures/2014/6/18/1403086345182/The-Avengers---2012-004.jpg","wordcount":"341","commentable":"true","byline":"Ben Child","productionO